</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1438,394,1727]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,318,1290,1316]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">Remarks.</emphasis>
We examined the 
<typeStatus box="[533,636,1290,1316]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[674,807,1291,1316]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Hermadion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[674,807,1291,1316]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">Hermadion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
? 
<emphasis box="[827,926,1291,1316]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">hyalinus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sars" box="[933,1119,1290,1316]" pageId="9" pageNumber="61" refString="Sars, G. O. (1873) Bidrag til kundskaben om dyrelivet paa vore havbanker. Forhandlinger i Videnskabs-selskabet i Christiania, 73 - 119." type="book chapter" year="1873">
G. 
<collectingCountry box="[960,983,1290,1316]" name="Iceland" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">O</collectingCountry>
. Sars, 
<number box="[1058,1119,1290,1316]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" value="1873.0">1873</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, an anterior fragment of 
<number box="[1406,1435,1290,1316]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" value="17.0">17</number>
segments, which according to an accompanying label has been checked by Pettibone in 
<number box="[1179,1238,1328,1354]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" value="1971.0">1971</number>
(and is therefore not included in her revision of 
<number box="[522,583,1365,1391]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" value="1969.0">1969</number>
) and referred by her to 
<taxonomicName authority="G.O. Sars, 1873" authorityName="G.O. Sars" authorityYear="1873" box="[867,1252,1365,1391]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Adyte" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hyalina">
<emphasis box="[867,1032,1365,1390]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">Adyte hyalina</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sars" box="[1049,1243,1365,1391]" pageId="9" pageNumber="61" refString="Sars, G. O. (1873) Bidrag til kundskaben om dyrelivet paa vore havbanker. Forhandlinger i Videnskabs-selskabet i Christiania, 73 - 119." type="book chapter" year="1873">
G. 
<collectingCountry box="[1077,1100,1365,1391]" name="Iceland" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">O</collectingCountry>
. Sars, 
<number box="[1179,1243,1365,1391]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" value="1873.0">1873</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. We agree with Pettibone's unpublished opinion, since the 
<typeStatus box="[667,772,1402,1428]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">holotype</typeStatus>
shows the main characters of the genus, except for the number of segments. Moreover, the comparison with the descriptions and figures of 
<taxonomicName authority="McIntosh, 1874" authorityName="McIntosh" authorityYear="1874" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Adyte" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="assimilis">
<emphasis box="[1243,1437,1440,1465]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">Adyte assimilis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="McIntosh" box="[159,351,1477,1503]" pageId="9" pageNumber="60" refString="McIntosh, W. C. (1874) XXVIII. On the invertebrate fauna and fishes of St. Andrews. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, series 4, 14, 192 - 207." type="journal article" year="1874">
McIntosh, 
<number box="[290,351,1477,1503]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" value="1874.0">1874</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Pettibone" box="[399,600,1477,1503]" pageId="9" pageNumber="60" refString="Pettibone, M. H. (1969) Review of some species referred to Scalisetosus McIntosh (Polychaeta, Polynoidae). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 82, 1 - 30." type="journal article" year="1969">
Pettibone (
<number box="[528,590,1477,1503]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" value="1969.0">1969</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Barnich" box="[658,965,1477,1503]" pageId="9" pageNumber="59" refString="Barnich, R. &amp; Fiege, D. (2003) The Aphroditoidea (Annelida: Polychaeta) of the Mediterranean Sea. Abhandlungen der Senckenbergischen Naturforschenden Gesellschaft, 559, 1 - 167." type="journal article" year="2003">
Barnich and Fiege (
<number box="[895,958,1477,1503]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" value="2003.0">2003</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
showed that both species are identical, with the same 
<typeStatus box="[325,376,1514,1540]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">type</typeStatus>
of elytra covered by scattered papillae, neuropodia with a very typical truncate, rounded acicular lobe, and neurochaetae with a semi-lunar pocket and minutely bidentate or unidentate tips. 
<taxonomicName authority="McIntosh, 1874" authorityName="McIntosh" authorityYear="1874" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Adyte" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="assimilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">A. assimilis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="McIntosh" box="[273,469,1589,1615]" pageId="9" pageNumber="60" refString="McIntosh, W. C. (1874) XXVIII. On the invertebrate fauna and fishes of St. Andrews. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, series 4, 14, 192 - 207." type="journal article" year="1874">
McIntosh, 
<number box="[407,469,1589,1615]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" value="1874.0">1874</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
becomes a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="G.O. Sars, 1873" authorityName="G.O. Sars" authorityYear="1873" box="[854,1199,1589,1615]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Adyte" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hyalina" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[854,978,1589,1614]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">A. hyalina</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sars" box="[996,1190,1589,1615]" pageId="9" pageNumber="61" refString="Sars, G. O. (1873) Bidrag til kundskaben om dyrelivet paa vore havbanker. Forhandlinger i Videnskabs-selskabet i Christiania, 73 - 119." type="book chapter" year="1873">
G. 
<collectingCountry box="[1025,1049,1589,1615]" name="Iceland" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">O</collectingCountry>
. Sars, 
<number box="[1129,1190,1589,1615]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" value="1873.0">1873</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1207,1317,1589,1615]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1207,1317,1589,1615]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">n. comb.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, which is redescribed here.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="54" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1438,394,1727]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,540,1663,1689]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
Northeastern Atlantic, North Sea, Mediterranean Sea; in 
<quantity box="[1287,1432,1664,1690]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.51" metricValueMax="2.93" metricValueMin="0.09" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" unit="m" value="151.0" valueMax="293.0" valueMin="9.0">9 to 293 m</quantity>
; facultative commensal of echinoids.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
